語言學研究方法                           RESERCH METHODOLOGY:LINGUISTICS


  	This course is designed to provide graduate students with the following basic methodological skills needed for preparing and writing a research paper or an MA thesis. Students will learn how to design and carry out a linguistic research project of their interests and how to present their ideas by speaking and writing. Upon the completion of this course, students are expected to be able to conduct an independent academic research and to produce a research proposal or complete research paper acceptable in the field of linguistics or applied linguisticsWe will learn how to search for research topics and relevant literature, compile an annotated bibliogrophy, understand different research methodologies, and write a formal research proposal including an abstract, an introduction, a critical literature review, and a research method. We will also learn how to develop successful search strategies, locate key articles, prepare bibliographic information and notes, evaluate research reports, as well as synthesize research results.

課程教育目標 

A 強化外國文學、文化、語言學理論與知識 To enable students to improve their knowledge and theory in the fields of foreign literatures, cultures and linguisticsB 培育外國文學及語言學領域的專業教學與學術研究人才 To cultivate talented people specializing in teaching and research in the disciplines of foreign literatures and linguisticsC 訓練學生進行研究、撰寫學術論文的能力 To enable students to develop their capabilities for research and academic writingD 培養獨立整合及創意思考的能力，發展專業且獨特研究觀點 To enable students to cultivate their capabilities for independent integration and creativie thinking and  develop their professionalism and unique research perspectives 
課程基本素養與核心能力 

A 厚植人文素養及西洋文學文化涵養

E 熟稔各種理論基礎、收集分析文獻資料的能力

F 完成學術論文及批判性書寫的能力

I 獨立思考、團隊合作、創意研究及分析、解決問題的能力


